page_analysis.text_content:
Attached garages/carports site planning

• Attached garages must comply with same setbacks as main dwelling.

Note: Uncovered spaces must be located beyond the required frontyard and beyond the first 10' of the street-side yard.

Fig 33 Examples of site planning solutions for attached garages/carports

A 1-car garage with 2nd space (uncovered) located in the sideyard

B 1-car garage with 2nd space (uncovered) located in the driveway

C 2-car garage with no uncovered spaces

visual_elements.description: Three side-by-side site plan examples illustrating attached garages/carports configurations on different lot types. Each example shows a lot with labeled areas: 'Buildable area' (shaded light gray), 'Main dwelling' (darker gray), and parking structures (black boxes labeled '1-car attached' or '2-car attached'). The diagrams include lot lines, curbs, sidewalks, required setbacks (dashed lines), no-parking areas (hatched lines), and uncovered spaces (depicted with a car icon). The first two diagrams are labeled 'Interior lot example' and the third 'Corner lot example'. Each diagram shows front yard, rear yard, interior-side yard, and street-side yard boundaries. A 10' measurement is indicated on the street-side yard in the corner lot example. The diagrams correspond to three scenarios: A) 1-car garage with a second uncovered space in the sideyard, B) 1-car garage with a second uncovered space in the driveway, and C) 2-car garage with no uncovered spaces.
Gray shaded box containing a note: 'Note: Uncovered spaces must be located beyond the required frontyard and beyond the first 10' of the street-side yard.'
